Use the standard library
This is how to numerical_letter_grade of grades:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that n is grades's length
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this n times:
      Remember that g is item i in grades
      Remember that letter is ""
      When g is at least 4.000000, then:
         Remember that letter is "A+"
      But, if not:
         When g is at least 3.700000, then:
            Remember that letter is "A"
         But, if not:
            When g is at least 3.500000, then:
               Remember that letter is "A-"
            But, if not:
               When g is at least 3.000000, then:
                  Remember that letter is "B"
               But, if not:
                  When g is at least 2.700000, then:
                     Remember that letter is "B-"
                  But, if not:
                     When g is at least 2.000000, then:
                        Remember that letter is "C"
                     But, if not:
                        When g is at least 1.700000, then:
                           Remember that letter is "C-"
                        But, if not:
                           When g is at least 1.300000, then:
                              Remember that letter is "D"
                           But, if not:
                              When g is at least 1.000000, then:
                                 Remember that letter is "D+"
                              But, if not:
                                 Remember that letter is "F"
                              End when
                           End when
                        End when
                     End when
                  End when
               End when
            End when
         End when
      End when
      Add result to letter
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is result
